## Learned User Preferences

- State machines own lifecycle and state logic; UI clients send events only and never decide open/close; avoid ref/state for sync guards
- Folder icons in `chat-message-tool-list-directory` open the file explorer pane on desktop and no-op on mobile, mirroring the file-icon → editor-open pattern.
- User chat-message bubble height matches the focused textarea variant — overflow text stays invisible/unreachable until focus; never add an inner scrollbar in the collapsed state.
- Use `react-virtuoso` for virtualization, not `@tanstack/react-virtual`; follow patterns in `combobox-responsive.tsx`; when virtuoso size/measurement bugs surface (e.g. tiny chat-message bubbles for very long text), fix via the slicing approach (cap items measured per pass, hand off to the existing virtuoso scroller) rather than removing virtuoso — never trade away virtualization for a perf hit on long content
- Never blow away the entire IndexedDB database — user work is stored there
- Chat composer toolbar, model/kernel selector triggers, and other paired breakpoint UIs: apply the same visible/control changes to both desktop and mobile layouts (including `chat-textarea-desktop.tsx` / `chat-textarea-mobile.tsx` when split) when the feature exists on both; floating affordances on the active streaming user message (e.g. inline stop button) must be overlayed/absolutely-positioned, never reserve extra vertical space in the message layout, and reveal only on hover/focus of the active `chat-message` root; matching the model selector hover-card pattern applies to peer triggers like the kernel selector for parity; the entire chat composer wrapper must remain the click target for focusing the inner contenteditable textarea (regressions where padding/decorative regions stop forwarding focus are real DX bugs)

