g ownership: `<ChatInstanceRegistry>` (`apps/ui/app/hooks/chat-instance-registry.ts`) is an in-memory registry of live `<ChatInstance>` mounts owned by `<ChatRegistryProvider>` (`apps/ui/app/hooks/chat-registry-provider.tsx`) at the app shell with per-chatId scoped subscriptions and stable snapshot refs (no `useSyncExternalStore` tearing); `<ChatInstance>` (`apps/ui/app/hooks/chat-instance.tsx`) owns `useChat` + `chatPersistenceMachine` + streaming/RPC and self-registers; `<ActiveChatProvider>` (`apps/ui/app/hooks/active-chat-provider.tsx`) is a per-subtree binding to the currently active chat for chat-input UIs (composer, message editor) and owns only the `draftMachine` in real (`chatId`) or ephemeral (`undefined`) mode — marketing/homepage routes pass `undefined` to skip IndexedDB writes; `<GlobalChatFlushGuard>` (`apps/ui/app/components/global-chat-flush-guard.tsx`) is a single app-shell flush guard that fans out `flushNow` to every registered chat's persistence + draft actors on page unload, replacing per-route `FlushOnCloseGuard`/`HomepageChatFlushOnCloseGuard`; one `ChatRegistryProvider` mounted near `root.tsx` works for every route (project, homepage, marketing) — no forked provider for non-project routes; chat composer accepts dragged viewer panes (`chat-viewer-dockview.tsx`) by invoking `capture-view-screenshot.utils.ts` to attach the current pane view as a chat image, and dragged editor tabs become `file-link` pills — drag detection routes through type-stamped data-transfer signatures in `chat-input-drop-handler.ts` and the entire `chat-textarea.tsx` is the drop target (not just the inner contenteditable area); the same `capture-view-screenshot.utils.ts` powers a camera button in `chat-viewer-controls.tsx` (`capture-view-control.tsx`) that captures the current pane view to active chat images on click; sticky-user-message-per-turn lives in `chat-history.tsx` by grouping each user message with its trailing assistant message into a turn-pair container that vi